11:
Time to eat, drink and be merry!
Even the esteemed Whitetail will be
joining us!
15:
Sorry, bro! We've gotta go run some
errands, so we need to hold off for
now!
19:
Huh?! Errands? You just promised
free booze, that's it!
24:
You can drink all you want when
we're done! Please, Bro. I really need
your help!
27:
Don't worry! All we gotta do is briefly
visit the folks working on the oil field
project, their nearby village, a
mousefolk village, and the dogfolk
town!
34:
And how'd you end up with an outfit
like that, anyway?
42:
Pretty sweet kimono, right? I had it

45:
I mean, it does look pretty good on
you.
49:
I just said told 'em I wanted to look
real fancy, and the tailor got super
into it! Turned out awesome!
51:
The tailor said they're interested in
clothing from other cultures, so
we're planning on establishing a
trade route from our world to theirs!
54:
I wanted you to dress in a more
dignified fashion...
56:
Haha... Well, I'm glad things around
here are peaceful enough where our
leaders can have a little fun with
their attire.
61:
Yup, yup! Even though we're still
experimenting with methods, we're
already digging the fields for burny
gloop!
64:
Before long, we'll have a full-blown
energy revolution on our hands!
73:
S-sir! People from the nearby village
are demanding to speak with you!
77:
I guess things were a little worse
than I thought.
81:
What'll you do? If you think violence

86:
Our martial aid shouldn't be
necessary here.
89:
Isn't that right, Claudius Navelle?
You are a man who fights his battles

94:
...Heh, yep! I planned for this. Any

99:
Looks like they're here! Let's go see

103:
Stop digging for burny gloop! Use
that money you're throwing to the
dogs and give us some food,

106: Hey, everybody! You're just in time!
110:
One more time...
Happy New Year!
114:
All right, gather 'round! Let's all ring
in the new year with a drink!
116:
We've got food too. Let's have a

121:
We were already going to visit and

124:
The dogfolk, birdfolk, mousefolk... We

127:
It sure wasn't cheap... But if we
manage to dig up some of that
burny gloop, we'll be back in the

130:
Y-you're still digging that stupid

135:
You want to handle the money
however you see fit, right? If that's

138:
However, that'll mean giving up your

But that's no fun, right?
144:
We've got a lot of work ahead of us.
Won't you lend us a hand?
150:
Yeesh! What a tough start to the
new year! We've still only dealt with

153:
...I was certain they would attack us

157: Even if they did, we'd protect you.
160:
But why were they so angry in the

164:
Well, an ambitious leader can do a

167:
Did you know that it's possible to

170:
Those two things depend on
effective and capable resource
management, which the village
chief is excellent at.
180:
...The chief here asked Nevia to look

came here.
